                            <comment id="13154986" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 09:58:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the problem also when starting? eg the log above shows that only r1 is stopped.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155004" author="julian.cable" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 10:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Claus, in the example, r1 will start and stop on schedule whereas r2 stays active always.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Julian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155216" author="bibryam" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 15:57:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ScheduledRoutePolicy was working only with one route (the first one assigned) at a time. I tried to fix that by introducing a map (a little bit refactoring) to store the routes using the same policy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Julian, can you give it a try?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155343" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 18:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Bilgin for the patch. Keep up the good work. Its been noticed you great work for the community.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155537" author="julian.cable" created="Tue, 22 Nov 2011 22:53:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fantastic, Thanks guys. I&apos;ll put a dev build together and try it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Julian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
